# ðŸŒ³ 100. Same Tree

ðŸ”— LeetCode Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/same-tree/

---

## ðŸ“Œ Problem Summary

Given the roots of two binary trees `p` and `q`, check if they are **identical**.

Two trees are the same if:
- They have the same structure  
- They have the same values at each node  

---

## ðŸ§  Core Idea

Use **recursion (DFS)** to compare:

Root â†’ Left subtree â†’ Right subtree

---

### âœ… Base Cases

| Condition | Result |
|----------|--------|
| Both nodes are `null` | `true` |
| One is `null` | `false` |
| Values differ | `false` |

---

## âœ… Recursive Java Solution

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isSameTree(TreeNode p, TreeNode q) {

        if (p == null && q == null) return true;

        if (p == null || q == null) return false;

        if (p.val != q.val) return false;

        return isSameTree(p.left, q.left) &&
               isSameTree(p.right, q.right);
    }
}
